Complaint Description: To The Sr.DME, Danapur Division, ECR  Subject : No watering is done in passenger coaches / toilets of MEMU train 03396/95 at PNBE, refer to my previous grievance MORLY/E/2022/06242 dated 31 March 2022, where the provided resolution was - "Due to operation constraints 03396/95 fully watering at PNBE."  Respected sir,  Kindly go through the RTI reply by PIO, DNR, ECR, which clearly states that MEMU train 03396 has link with another MEMU train 03379. Kindly note that between the arrival time of MEMU 03379 (10:30) and departure time of MEMU 03396 (10:35), there is a small gap of 5 minutes, and the train rake is supposed to halt at PNBE just for those 5 minutes.  Now, please let me know which super efficient team / staff of mechanical department at PNBE junction connects the hydrant pipes at PNBE platform within 5 minutes of time and complete the watering process to ensure water availability in coaches of 03396 / 03395?  Your statement stands incorrect - "No watering is done in this train's rake", this is for your kind information please.  Now, coming back your point that watering in MEMU coaches is done once in a day, in your words - "03396/95 is being watered at PNBE during its trip journey. MEMU coaches are being watered at their originating stations once in a day." Neither 03396 nor 03395 get watered at PNBE or IPR. So as the complaint is regarding the watering of coaches to ensure water availablity in the toilets of 03396/95, you must have HYDRANT pipes at IPR platform number 1. Or, if your operations team can place train 03396 at PF3 of IPR for refilling of water, that will also be great for us passengers.  kind regards, Gaurav Bhartiya, Islampur
